caption: Amazing
The filet was amazing , perfectly sizzled!!! Duck 3 ways and the bacon infused foam.. .unforgettable!!! I will fly to Honolulu just for this place!  <3
Good Asian food but it is a little pricy
Meh.  It still reminds me of a gym.  The food was good - not great.  Lots of hype for so-so grub.  As for drinks - you can do better at your local Costco.

The Iron Chef should be embarrassed! This place has a great location, the Waikiki beach, sunset, people watching,  etc. We sat near the balcony to catch the sunset and we  each ordered appetizers. 1st was the garlic shrimp (5 med. Shrimp), 2nd was the Dim Sum, and 3rd was the Jelly Fish.  Dim sum was so- so. Jelly Fish was different and crunchy like a pickle but lighter in taste, and the Garlic shrimp was good and tasty , but not worth the price. Menu listings were pricey, for example the 1/2 of duck was  $60 (whole duck can be had for $20 all day at any decent Asian Restaurant in ), the Tomahawk steak $120, and that's about $25 at Sams club. I ordered the steak ( $60) and it's A La Carte, so rice was ordered as well. The steak was too sweet, must be the sweet soy sauce and it wasn't worth $60. I live on Florida's Gulf Coast and we have some great restaurants and I know my food. Why 1 star? It's this.  You are in a nice restaurant,  beautiful view of the beach and sunset, but about 150 feet from the balcony their is a Pavilion that becomes a haven for the  Urban campers, i.e. the Hlomeless. I know Hawaii is a liberal state and I saw two uniformed cops making rounds so it was SOP  for the Homeless to sleep there but with the mutual  understanding that they must vacate in the morning before the tourists. Well as I was in my 2nd bite of that sweet steak, a homeless woman goes towards the wall, hikes up her skirt,  and does a halfway squat and does her business right there * the Pavilion is lit up very bright*. I pointed that out to my companions and also looked at the reactions from other diners and it was as expected...disgust and disbelief. Keep in mind that she could have gone to the beach  and into the darkness. I mentioned what I saw to the waiter and he wasn't fazed by it at all. Again,  great view, So- So food that was way overpriced, but until the politicians do something about adequate housings for the homeless I wouldn't eat there. Morimoto   needs to retrain these Chefs and your name can only bring you a one time visit from the likes of me. As for all these 5 stars review... I'm shaking my head...right...

Really good food and impeccable service. They were slightly over staffed to make sure you were never left wanting. Cocktails are spendy, but that's par for the course at all high end restaurants. Excellent portion sizes. I should have had left overs, but it tasted too good!
Delicious food, excellent service!

The service was great! The food came out as it was ready, some taking longer than others due to cooking preference. The flaming chocolate dessert was a sight to see, but sadly didn’t taste how it looked... so I would stick with the pog sherbet!
Nice food, good flavours.  Service not as good as I expected at a place claiming to be high end.  Nice to go, but there are better places where you have more attentive staff and better food.
Heyyy..Where do I start? I loved the beef carpaccio appetizer to start my feast, and my sake mojito! I also loved my ishiiyaki hamachi!
Pretty good place for tests. The dishes is very interesting. I recommend and will come back again.
Over-priced average food in small portions is not an ideal place to dine to me.
Great food and service! Loved the ocean view and welcome atmosphere!

Went on a Friday night, wasn’t busy at all. Space is cool and massive, but somehow got seated towards the back. I ordered the shrimp pad Thai and there was more food than I expected, which was okay. Not sure if I’d go back for the food. I will say the service was outstanding and attentive.

Such a disappointing restaurant and honestly a disgrace for Morimoto to sign off his name on this restaurant. It's essentially Panda Express but you have to pay more (And I honestly would rather go to Panda Express 'value + taste' in mind). I understand this supposed to be influenced or an homage to "Asian" cuisine but being Asian myself this is an insult and a sad pandering to the North American market. DISGUSTING don't go.

Morimoto Asia is a delight. Its a delicious fusion between Chinese and Japanese cuisine. The restaurant is located on the second floor of the Alohilani hotel. Beautiful ambience with a choice between indoor and outdoor seating. But the entire restaurant has a clear gorgeous view of the Waikiki beach. We were here at sunset. Great food  and great view. Try the mocktails. My favorite was the Lillikoi slush with lychee. The popcorn shrimp is amazing. Love the house fried rice. Try the dimsum sampler. Loved this place.
Amazing Japanese food with an Asian influence

My Husband and I decided to splurge on a fancy dinner while visiting Waikiki! We had the pleasure of staying the the Alohilani Resort, where the hotel is located. Admittedly, I was  a bit nervous that I would be disappointed, but the food and service was fantastic. Our server, Manu, was very helpful and fun. My husband and I shared the Sticky ribs as an appetizer, then shared the black Cod and crispy fish, and a bottle of Sake. Everything was delicious, but we really loved the Black Cod. I would recommend visiting Morimoto Asia if looking for fancy night out in Waikiki!
The surf and turf is phenomenal.
Ramen was some of the best ive ever had. Great food, service, & atmosphere. Worth going.
My friend really enjoys this place for her birthday celebration for last two years. All staffs are very attentive and friendly. Foods are great. Also we love nice sunset too.

So many celebrity restaurants are a disappointment... thankfully this restaurant was a pleasant surprise! The food, service, and atmosphere were top notch. It's served family style and there is an amazing selection of food. I recommend trying a hot appetizer and a cold one then share an entree for a party of two. This was more than enough food and we couldn't finish it all, but we got a really good selection of a variety of foods.

(Translated by Google) I was taken care of by an employee trip.  The dishes were all very elaborate and very delicious.  The restaurant is very friendly and the staff can stay with peace of mind.  I think that it is the top class restaurant among many restaurants in Hawaii ☆  In addition, we will use it by all means. Food was ok, guess they have a dress code, didnt know. Didnt explain and made me sit in the bar area cuz I wasnt wearing a shirt with sleeves. Took over an hour to get food which was ok but everything comes out at different times. The manager was very cool and accommodating
The sticky beef is awesome.

(Translated by Google) The atmosphere is very good, especially from the terrace, where you can see the sea and take pictures. The tables at all seats are large and easy to sit. The quality of the clerk is also good, and I like the style of seeing the kitchen. The price is not very high, and the rice is almost the same as in Japan and delicious. Seasoning of shrimp and pork ribs is the best and I repeat during my stay. For the dessert, the banana pudding is very delicious and impressive.  (Original) 雰囲気もとてもよく、特にテラス席からは海も見えて写真を撮るのにも良いです。全ての席のテーブルも大きくて座りやすいです。店員さんの質もよく、厨房が見えるスタイルも気に入っています。 お値段もあまり高くなく、お米もほぼ日本と同じで美味しいです。シュリンプや豚のリブの味付けが最高で滞在中にリピしてます。デザートはバナナのプリンがとても美味しくて感動です。

This place boasts a modern decor that feels trendy, yet comfortable at the same time. The service is good. The best part, however, is the food. A particularly memorable dish is the whole, fried fish. It is spectacular.

Beyond unreal food! The duck is second to none.  The bbq black cod melts in your mouth. Went one night had to come back the next it was so good. Fish carpaccio, sushi, did I mention the crispy PORK BELLY? This place is everything you would expect from an iron chef. The staff is on point and a big part of the experience.  If there was one con to the whole place it would be  there are too many options on the menu for me to try it all before I head home. Don't miss this place.
(Translated by Google) Delicious!!!!  (Original) Delicioso!!!!
Food all around is amaze balls! Definitely try the sticky ribs; absolutely worth it!
Amazing food! My favorite Waikiki restaurant and I can’t wait to go back.

(Translated by Google) This restaurant is just supervised by the American version of the iron cook Chef Morimoto. I thought that it was a fusion of Japanese cuisine, and it was just like trying to add curry powder to typical dishes from Asian countries and adding some tricks to make it a novel style. Hamachi tartar was too confusing because the hamachi became too fine. First of all, the calamari salad of squid was stuffy because the squid was funyahunya and the clothes were peeled off. Curry flour in Singapore curry flour was too effective and could not be eaten until the end. The idea may be good, but the skill of the creator is immature. The view from the deck is amazing. I can't find a better place. I want you to do your best with the taste of cooking.  (Original) アメリカ版料理の鉄人シェフのモリモトさんが監修してるだけ、のレストラン。 日本料理のフュージョンかと思いきや、アジア各国の代表的な料理にカレー粉入れたり、なんか小技を足して斬新風、にしてみただけって感じ。 ハマチのタルタルは、ハマチが細かくなり過ぎててよくわからなくなってた。 イカのカラマリサラダは、まず、イカがフニャフニャで、衣が剥がれてるのがあってべちゃっとしてた。 シンガポールカレー粉ビーフンはカレー粉が効きすぎてて、辛くて最後まで食べきれなかった。 アイディアはいいのかもしれないけど、作る人の技術が未熟な感じ。 デッキからの眺めは最高です。それくらいしかいいところが見つからない。料理の味でもっと頑張ってほしい。
It's an Iron Chef restaurant.  Nothing else needs to be said
Great food, great cocktails. Friendly staff. A little pricey but worth it if you’re looking for good Asian food in Waikiki. Recommend the Smokey old fashioned cocktail and sushi for food.
I love it, get A5 here omg 😭💕
Delicious, but admittedly overpriced for what you get.
Honestly, the best dining experience I have ever had. The food and service are amazing. Aaron our waiter was next level. My go to restaurant every time I come back to Oahu. Mahalos !
Zero Japanese spirit or care to the food.

Great service but really over priced! Fried rice was a little oily. Orange chicken was okay. Rib appie was delicious but only yielded 3 ribs so it seemed a little over priced for what one paid and was served. Nice venue though.
Tremendous food
The food was excellent. Out of everything we got the sticky ribs were the best. They make their own ginger beer for their mules and it was surprisingly spicy (not bad, just surprising).
Great food, portion sizes were bigger than expected and atmosphere was great.  All together an awesome dinner!
I would skip getting another “frozen beer” but I was great to try. 5-7pm is Happy Hour and very inexpensive for Waikiki joints. Great Ramen and will eat there again!!!
So nice eating with Waikiki beach in view! The drinks are different and nice...but of course the food is delicious and pretty. Lots of pictures and instagram worthy meals. We had a nice time~

I wanted to like this place, but the critical reviews are accurate. The food really is only ok, the restaurant tries to have food from a lot of different Asian cuisines (hence Asia in the name) and every dish is done better by a restaurant that focuses on that one cuisine. People raved about the surf and turf roll, and it's not great. Kalbi was tender but the flavour was just kochujang. House fried rice was ok, but again didn't pack much flavour. Black cod was kind of good, but done better elsewhere.  As others have said, the service isn't that good either. I'm not a guy that needs the servers to appear instantly whenever I need them but basic things weren't done. We ordered the A5 Wagyu beef and didn't get a knife and fork. Eating The fried rice off large dishes with chopsticks is also awkward, they should probably give bowls with the dish. Also dishes that we finished didn't get cleared the whole meal. The men's bathroom had a single urinal that was pretty gross, but that's to be expected if 200 guests share that one urinal, they probably could've added a few more urinals, or they need someone to clean it constantly.  If your wallet is fat and expectations low, you can probably enjoy this place.

Awesome food, awesome vibes. Nicely priced (seafood items such as lobster understandably more expensive).  Also they ask if you celebrate something special which is awesome. A definite recommendation in Waikiki

The banana dessert was fantastic and the duck pretty solid (although I prefer tradition bao buns over a tortilla)...  everything else was ok.  If was like 2/3 the price it would be 4.5 stars, but definitely overpriced for what you get.
This dessert made my year. The Jason Momoa look-a-like server was an added bonus.
Get the meatballs! Best thing on the menu.. (Probably) And the mule is good!

Loved the food! Atmosphere was amazing. Been there twice, Stephanie and Emily were so much fun and personable, I would come in again just for them. I have to give a special shout out to Jen, our waitress, for taking such good care of us! Everything was perfect. Ian the manager was a true gentleman, made us feel like family. I will be coming back with my family and my boss.
Great atmosphere, food, libations, and awesome staff.
Upscale asian dining

Ok, awesome restaurant great vibe. The food is excellent. Had the Fish sashimi excellent. Then the Kobe beef which you heat  over a hot rock fun  experience. 😀 The  only down side is I sat at the bar which lacked attention to detail and follow through.  i.e had to flag the waiter  for another drink, did not get my rice with entree order. WaIted 15 minutes for chocolate ice cream dessert.  I spent $200 for one person. I do expect a little better. And I know they can step up. For that I gave them 4 stats but I  will be back.

Though all dishes were flavorful, I felt, especially for those sensitive to salt and oil, most of them were salty to excess (if I were to return, I’d definitely request sauces on the side). Other than that, the dishes were colorful and beautifully presented!

Excellent service! The food here is delicious. We tried the Singapore noodles, basil fried rice, veggie soba noodles, dragon roll, shrimp tempura roll. The king pao chicken is average. Highly recommend this restaurant.
Delicious food! Amazing appetizers. Wagyu beef roll was the mind blowing with such an idea. Highly recommend!!
Great food, service and atmosphere.
This is a great restaurant with top quality food and preparation. This is my 6th time in Hawaï and possibly the best food I have had.
Sticky ribs and duck Caeser salad were fantastic! Definitely would go back.
Great food.
(Translated by Google) The sunset seen from the terrace seats is beautiful  (Original) テラス席から見えるサンセットが美しいです
Amazing food and service. Are here a few times and was never disappointed.

I expected wayyyyy more from a celebrity chef owned restaurant.  The service was pretty unprofessional.  They never cleared away the hot towels from the table and they didn't take our menus after ordering so they sat next to me the whole time and our server was wayyyyy too chatty.  The food was also very disappointing...it just wasn't that good.  This place is very expensive for what it is...Don't waste your money here!!!

It was okay. The pork belly appetizer (fried and silvered into halves) was nothing special and probably not the best way to serve pork belly. The hot stone bowl was lacking in unique textures and flavors. Instead it heavily relied on the sauce to make up for what could have been a good dish. Bit of a disappointing food experience but the service was fantastic and prompt.
Wonderful experience.  Great service by Kendall.
Best meal we had in Hawaii all week. Food was amazing, great service and dessert was a treat
The food is great, but don't expect interesting sushi rolls.
From the service to the food, everything was spectacular. Would definitely recommend sitting outside for the best experience.
Service and food are excellent and the sunset view from the patio was stellar!  Highly recommended!

Great menu with lot of famous Asian dishes. Cantonese, Japanese, Singaporean and Hawaiian. Best roast duck I've had in the states. If you're looking for "Hawaii butterfish", try their BBQ black cod, it also comes with a bed of sauteed Chinese broccoli & baby bok choy. The restaurant also have an excellent hospitality.

The food was excellent, the service was excellent and they explained how to eat my whole fish and spicy dishes they suggested having the sauce on the side. There was a mix up with my whole fish so the manager gave us free beers. Our salad was served at table side where they put it together, it was the duck ceasar salad, very fresh. I recommend this restaurant.
Great food, plus great view of a magnificent sunset.

We decided to go last minute because we had a open night and realized how close it was from where we are staying. We loved loved food and menu when it was at the modern hotel - and we have eaten at the napa location also —and was so excited to see this open Food and drinks did not disappoint!! Wish there were some things from the other menu that carried over but again (Tempura pineapple please !!!) amazing. Big complaint is the service was beyond unacceptable and it was a slow thurs night I know this sounds extreme but it might be the worst most neglectful service I can recall in a long time. Staff supplementing our ‘server’ might be the only reason we left a tip and that’s not me. We are huge fans of chef and loved the food but all I can do is shake my head at the service it was of poor quality. We had the pad Thai and whole fish was amazing it’s debonded crusted and and had great flavor. The only other negative is - and this isn’t really against the restaurant but wow There was maybe a pre wedding group or office that was SO drunk and loud and yelling and using the most inappropriate language and describing inappropriate acts it made us want to leave and not order more drinks or dessert. We couldn’t leave fast enough except wait — our wait person was MIA so it was 17 min after our plates were cleared we even were offered anything else. We actually saw a dessert on social media we planned to order and my husband really wanted another drink - he had a smoked old fashioned made tableside that was amazing - but again we were never check on or offered ... we thought maybe we ask to have dessert in the bar away from the disruptive party but again no. I will say the staff person attending to the party did ask them to please be polite and know this is a family establishment and respect the noise and language but seconds later it went unattended.  I’m sadly disappointed but loved the food and chef so that won me over
Great atmosphere and very worldly food!!
Amazing. View, atmosphere, drinks, high quality food and service. Highly recommend!
deserve to visit. a bit spicy but not bad at all.
Great restaurant with a spectacular view of the sunset if that’s your thing.  Food is excellent!!! Would definitely recommend.

Nothing special, waiter said it’s a free complimentary dessert for a bday person and only after reminding him about it after finished the dinner, he said ok and brought the smallest scoop of nasty ice cream.
Great food and excellent service.
The food was great! but is it really ethical for the waiter to ask for a higher tip if the waiter wasn't so great severing our food. I'm I right to give the waiter a bad tip or I'm I wrong?
Awesome food and lively atmosphere

(Translated by Google) The appetizers seemed to be delicious, but the main fish dishes and meat dishes were often seasoned like Chinese dishes and I felt it wasn't very good for the Japanese.  (Original) 前菜は美味しそうな料理がありましたが、メインの魚料理、肉料理は中華料理のような味付けの料理が多くて、日本人にはあまり美味しくないと感じました。
I really can't say enough about this place. I'm usually hesitant to eat out in a tourist area but Morimoto's lived up to the hype. Surf and turf sushi roll was amazing!!
The exsperiance was awesome. Highly recommend the restaurant. Service was outspending.
Tuna pizza!!!
Some of the best food I've ever had. Try the popcorn shrimp and A5 steak. Service was impeccable
I tried this place twice, I didn't like it both times. Nice ambiance and nice service,  the food just wasn't up to par

Dinner was awesome.  For appetizers we ordered the Assored Dim Sum Sampler and a Spicy Tune Roll. For the main course we ordered the Grilled Kalbi and the Ga Prao Rice. Both were cooked to perfection and tasted awesome.  The service was great.  We woukd definitely come back here.
Amazing service...better food!

I have mixed feelings towards this restaurants. Here is why: - The Kirin (slushy beer) was not even chilled enough (let alone being frozen). - The Hot and Sour soup was great, - The House Greens Salad was good (the orange segments give a unique taste to it), - The Spicy Salmon Sushi was OK (compare to what we always get in Vancouver, Canada), - The Jellyfish was good too, - The edamame was average. The portions are fairly small (you probably would expect that for a fine restaurant- so don’t trust the “for share” section on the menu since most of the are barely enough for one person) The ambience is great and the service is fantastic.
More food focused than sushi focused than his Vegas location (if that makes sense). Service was friendly and the food didn’t disappoint.
Loved the lobster tempura roll, also the orange chicken was good. Great food and view. Just a little slow to refill my tiny water cup, which is a big pet peeve of mine at nicer restaurants.

Everything you would expect from an Iron Chef.   Delicious food presented spectacularly.  Inventive dishes.  Accommodating and knowledgeable staff. Best sushi I've tasted.  The rice was perfect. Excellent duck dish demonstrated tableside.  The chocolate sphere was brilliant and delicious. Even simple banana pudding was elevated. Pricey but worth it.

We had dinner here for our 25th wedding anniversary. We loved the food, wine and service. Chairs were comfortable and everything worked like clockwork. Nothing was too much trouble. Thank you - we will be back again one day.
Absolutely incredible food and service! Beautiful atmosphere. Highly recommend trying the Chocolate Sphere dessert!
With spectacular sunset views from the 3rd floor, Morimoto Asia Waikiki was a delicious spot for great sushi, dim sum, and cocktails. Book a table at sunset and enjoy great service!

From the famed chef, Morimoto, I wouldn't expect anything less. The food was on point! We got yellow tail sushi rolls and short ribs. Both were exceptional. They have really good Japanese whiskey and delicious cocktails. The staff was very knowledgable about the menu, as well!

Great food and service. The ingredients taste top shelf and the presentation was great. M Our server daniel b was very attentive and well mannered. This place is expensive but worth the go if you are looking for something upscale. Would definetly go back.
Amazing food but it is pricey
Amazing good food, the sushi is also very good
Amazing table side service. Super friendly waitstaff and delicious food. The price is very reasonable for the quality of the food you get.
Best value in Waikeke
Staff was fantastic and food is excellent. Their staff and wait staff's attention to detail and service are second to none. Will return again.
Nice location however the food is not worth the price.
WOW!
Great food. Mix of Asian cuisines. BBQ cod, gyoza, sticky ribs and sushi are all delicious options. Reasonably priced considering it's location
Not authentic, had better dinners.
Portions are so small, the entrees are supposed to be shared but its ridiculously overpriced for the food. Service is good though.

Foods were ok. Various Asian fine dine. Nice place to be at,  kinda indoor/outdoor combo so it's not exactly cool inside. A shorts and tshirt warmth in a loud room for dinner. The waiters really have to work it and they service the tables well so they look a little sweaty. So I guess the only thing fine dine about Morimoto Asia is the price.
Great food, great atmosphere
Excellent restaurant from start to finish. Stay for the flaming end to the meal!

The food was super tasty!!! The reason for a 4 star is because of the incident we had at the front desk. When we made a reservation online there was no info about a dress code, so since it is Hawaii my husband wore a tank top, because of that we got snobby attitude from the front desk, which made my husband feel super uncomfortable. We have no problem following a dress code as long as we are aware of it and not made feel like we are peasants lol After informing one of the servers about the situation she apologized and got us a free beer. Other than that incident everything was great! Definitely go, but keep in mind they have a dress code.
(Translated by Google) Top! Absolutely recommended.  (Original) Spitze! Absolut zu empfehlen.

My wife and I had the pleasure of eating here tonight. We had the sticky ribs, a must have! For our entree we shared the house fried rice and the fried whole fish.  We finished the chocolate sphere. Everything was absolutely delicious.  The staff and service was bar none. They're very knowledgeable and courteous.
very very good
Had takeout...can only vouch for food. Excellent!!!!!! Had variety of sushi rolls..recommend.

Our favourite meal in Hawaii by far was at the Morimoto Asia restaurant. All the food was absolutely incredible and fresh, Gyoza was delicious, drinks were definitely worth the price. Our server was extremely friendly and provided the entire fine dining experience exceptionally. We will most definitely be back on our next trip to Waikiki beach!

Great location, great service, just don't order the Wagyu steak!! At US$168 for one piece of steak, it was the most expensive and average steak I have ever ordered anywhere in the world! We were looking forward to returning for a 3rd time until we received the bill.
food and service ace

The food and drinks were fantastic and the location is amazing. We sat on the patio dining room area overlooking Waikiki Beach, amazing views. The service was top notch. Recommend experiencing the variety of food available.
Good happy hour prices, average selection and quality

Happy hour has great prices. The wagyu sliders are delicious. Off the regular menu we ordered orange chicken & fried rice, very good as well, & able to share. Staff is extremely attentive & friendly. Would definitely come here again.

The staff is super lovely and the restaurant is beautiful and spaced out. Very lovely lounge vibe. MUST TRY the banana pudding!!!! It was incredibly delicious I had no idea it had so many layers each one being even more delicious!!! So so good. My only down point would be that the tofu with sauteed veggie wok wasn't as exciting. As a vegetarian it is very hard to find good restaurants and this meal could have been so much more exciting. Which is why I give only 4 starts. Apart from that the coktail menu is great and the blueberry cocktail I had was yummy and refreshing. The menu itself was very appealing (if you eat meat!!)
This is one of my favorite places in Waikiki. The happy is one of the best in town.

Service ○ Almost no customer, no Japanese, and employees can not speak Japanese. If there are many overseas people, it may be appropriate for the response. Over charged almost twice as much for items, food tasted terrible and was overpriced for the quality of it. Honestly so bad we had to laugh about it.

Dinner with sake was delicious. Dave recommended the spicy egg rolls and tantan and duck ramen. How wonderful to not have to worry about the first time selection. Worthy of many more visits. His service was unpretentious, friendly and professional. Thanks Dave.

(Translated by Google) Very good oriental food, excellent service and attention. There is very soft background music, electronic type, the setting is very much in tune with the place. The price the same. I recommend.  (Original) Riquisima comida bien oriental, excelente servicio y atencion. Hay musica de fondo muy suave, tipo electrónica, la ambientación esta muy acorde al lugar. El precio lo mismo. Recomiendo.
Great atmosphere, great service, food is good.
Great place for dinner! Love the design and deserts!

Three stars.  If you have watched Morimoto on Iron Chef America,  you will notice his clean yet excellent choices of meal on the show.  We were expecting similar clean and unique dishes at a restaurant that bore his name.  Sadly this is an Americanized restaurant.  Dishes are designed to cater the tastes of the masses.  I believe Morimoto may have a unique shop else where that focuses on his trademark clean and unique dishes.  But the Waikiki location is on part with the usual Asian style restaurants.  It's good and worth your money, just don't expect dishes like Morimoto would make on Iron Chef America.    Bon Appetit!

We were searching for a place to eat and saw this place. We had no reservation and had to wait around 5min at 8pm for a place outside. The food came after 5-10min. The service is super friendly and the food is very delicious!! I had noodle plate with pork and vegetables for 17$. That was a super price for that delicious food. Highly recommend!!!
Just enjoyed a delicious dinner here. Lovely view and excellent service. Had the sticky ribs, duck Caesar salad and garlic shrimp with some steamed rice. All exceptional!

Kind of ovverrated place by Waikiki Beach. I got a fish, which turned out to be very small for an expensive price. Dessert was also average (banana pudding) for the price. People are friendly.

Simply put, the Tuna Pizza paired with the Riesling was one of the best meals I've ever eaten. Amazing flavors. I also had the Miso soup and the yellowfin sushi roll, both were superb. The whole meal came to about $50 which was well worth it. I may go back before the week is done.

Food is excellent, the ahi pizza is my personal favorite and the Kirin beer with the the beer slush on the top goes down to easy. Our waiter Michael took good care of us, EXCELLENT service Michael, Thank You!!!

Absolutely loved it, we accidentally booked the wrong date but the kind staff would let us in on the right day instead, the kitchen staff prepares very good food and loved the little shows they do at the table telling you how to proper eat the food and make it ready!
Great service and food were delicious.

We came here for dinner and Erin our server helped make it a great experience.  The menu is very varied and adapts to different dietary restrictions.  We had the sticky ribs as an appetizer they were absoljutely delicious crunchy on the outside and uicy inside with a great sweet sauce, the only down side is that it comes  with 3 make it very weird for sharing.  For Entrees we had the Crispy Whole Fish wich was alright, nothing too special and it left my boyfriend still hungry after dinner since it doesnt come with any sides. I had the ishiyaki buri bop, the presentation was amazing as it is seared on the table, but flavour wise it was very average. Too much rice for the meat ratio and seemed likke it lack flavor in my opinion.  It is average in price with other similar restaurants in the area.
Excellent food. However service not very professional.
Amazing food and atmosphere.

The waygu beef and and lobster sushi is incredible.  Highly recommend. We went for a birthday and we're very impressed.  This guys IS the Iron Chef, so of course his meals were creative and beautifully plated.  Highly recommend for a night out in Waikiki or Blue Note
The happy hour food was delicious, and their blue berry drink was extremely delicious! Highly recommend!!!
Great service and food!! I had the tacos and the Singapore noodles and it was great!!! Next time I need to reserve a table so I can eat outside.

Disappointed with the service and the food. Many other smaller genuine Asia food locations like Chiba Ken in the area. Don’t waste your money.  We had issue with our food (hard chicken piece that almost broke a tooth) and manager couldn’t even come talk to us. We should of went to Roy’s.

Morimoto's previous restaurant was amazing, this place is like Panda Express with fancy plating and nice waiters. The "whole duck" was two legs and most of the breast, and it tasted like KFC. The rest of our meal was so boring I've actually forgotten which other dishes we ordered. Save your money and go eat a whole duck in Chinatown.

Expensive (though not terribly so for the area) and basically fine. Average sushi. The frozen beer was a nice little treat.
Great happy hour drinks!

Just wanted to say our waitress Deanna was fantastic. The restaurant and food were all delicious, but she was really what made it a 5 star experience. We had a particularly complicated order with all our family's different dietary restrictions and she handled it with ease. Thank you Deanna!
Authentic Food with a superb touch of Hawaiian flavor. Best part? Its right across waikiki beach where you can enjoy the view. Foods great, and my Boba bae is ❤️ Love her so much.
Not impressed for the price would have been equally satisfied ordering take out...made a rez and got a horrible table...decent service I guess

Had an amazing dinner here!  Wasn't sure what the frozen beer would be like, but tried it and it was great.  Tried several different dishes, the spicy tuna was really good, and the ishiyaki buri bop was great, it is made at your table and the server explained it as it cooked right in front of you.  Finished with the chocolate sphere, which was incredible...like the buri bop, it is finished at your table, where they melt a large chocolate sphere containing chocolate sorbet, which then coats the sorbet in a delicious chocolate shell.  It is worth coming back just to watch that again, in addition to the delicious food.

We had such an excellent meal here. The dining area is gorgeous. View of the water on Waikiki Beach so you can watch the sunset. Open kitchen concept so you can see what is happening. High ceilings and nice space between the tables.  For drinks, they have a few specialties. The smokey Manhattan is prepared at the table and a great version of the drink. The slushy Kiran is refreshing but a little strange.  For our appetizers, we tried the short ribs and dim sum sampler. Both were excellent and great for sharing. Really loved the short ribs!  For our mains, we shared a rainbow roll, Kung Pao Chicken, kalbi short ribs and chef Morimoto's signature dish (buri bop). Everything was excellent! Great for sharing! The buri bop is prepared at the table and is super fun to watch.  For dessert, we have the chocolate sphere and donuts. Beautiful presentation and delicious!! The sphere is prepared at the table as well.
Made a reservation; details got messed up and ended up waiting. Food was decent and overpriced. Only positive thing was friendly waiter and the sticky ribs. Would not come back.

We visited Morimoto Asia restaurant tonight and we were pleasantly impressed with the food and the service.  First of all, this is a lovely restaurant and has a large menu offering authentic Asian fare for reasonable prices. We ordered a few items since this was our first visit and everything was delicious and served quickly.  Our server Michael was super attentive and did a great job taking care of us! He took the time to explain the food and even offered a few recommendations.  The website says the dress code is “smart casual” but they do not enforce it. There were people wearing sports shorts, flip flops and one guy even had a dog with him. Imagine my husbands face when he saw this and I had told him to put on slacks and an aloha shirt! Not happy. The website specifically says no shorts, but lots of guests were wearing them in the main dining room area.  There was one big problem: We ordered Yakisoba with pork and it never arrived. Sadly, this was the one dish that my husband wanted tonight but for some reason the kitchen never made it and offered no explanation why. Our server had cleared the dishes from our table and it still hadn’t arrived so we asked him about it and he said that he would take it off of the bill and he didn’t know why the kitchen didn’t serve it. This was disappointing because we REALLY wanted to try the yakisoba, but everything else was delicious and I guess it was just overlooked. Michael removed it from our check.  If you only order one thing, I would strongly recommend the house fried rice!! It is full of flavor and my daughter especially loved the fresh edamame added to the dish.
Amazing food, staff and atmosphere! Highly recommend!
5 stars.

My husband and I ate at Morimoto Asia tonight for our anniversary/his birthday dinner and we absolutely loved it.  We had the A5 beef and the whole Branzino, along with some appetizers. We really enjoyed everything we ordered.  We would definitely recommend this restaurant.

This is a beautiful restaurant located across the street from Waikiki Beach. Beautiful views of the ocean in the beach. The restaurant has a wide selection on the menu. Everything we ordered tasted great. The staff was friendly and helpful, and they even provided entertainment. This is a great venue for a private party or dinner.  They feature a full bar, with indoor and outdoor seating.
SImply wow! We were here last week and the experience from service, to ambience, to food were just amazing!

We were excited to be going to an Iron Chef restaurant. But, this unfortunately was a really mixed experience. The maitre d' wasnt particularly friendly or welcoming, so that felt odd. The staff that served us were much more friendly but did not seem to know the menu, so that was also a mixed experience (basic questions about what was in the dish were met with 'let me go check'). The food was also a bit mixed. We had a blackened swordfish dish which was delicate and tasty, however, I can't really remember any of the other dishes so they were neither terrible, but nor were they great.  Overall, we spent upwards of USD200 for 2 people without actually being full - so we could have spent more but thankfully didnt. At that price, you always expect friendly, expert service with a smile, knowledge of product and excellent, consistent food. Yes, McDonald's can do it, so why can't you? The 3 stars is for the swordfish. The rest doesn't even deserve that much.
Food was as expected. Duck was a let down. Service was...unique. Server was over the top, a caricature of a server, straight out of the movie Office Space.
Went to the bar specifically to see Chef.bartender great on keeping a eye out.really nice bar and nice bartenders.have been here several times for happy hour
The Duck and the Short Ribs here were amazing. Everything was great!

We enjoyed our meal here tremendously. Each dish had exactly the right balance of flavours. Sweet, sour, spicy, and savoury but light enough to allow the fresh ingredients to shine. We had dumplings, hot and sour soup, pork ribs, pad Thai and sautéed vegetables plus a wonderful spicy chicken with egg on rice dish. Great beers and service. I highly recommend sitting outside to enjoy the view.
Great food pricey

I have been looking forward to eating here for a while. Huge Iron Chef nerd. We had a reservation at 8 and got seated soon after. Service was incredible and the ambiance of the place was fantastic. We ordered a little bit of everything and the portions were perfect for 2. Food was delicious and presentation is just what you would expect when you put your fancy pants on and go to a place like this. Would highly recommend Morimoto Asia.
Fantastic food , presentation and service! We will be back!

I love this place! We eat here as often as possible. The food is a fusion of many styles and served as family style (if you want to share). Very popular and reservations are highly suggested. The wait staff is friendly and helpful with suggestions. They will let you know if you are ordering too much food (or not enough!). We never leave hungry or unsatisfied.
Disappointing second visit here. Appetizer was served at same time as entree. Disappointing.  Entree was not hot.
Good service great food not busy

Really enjoyed the Ishiyaki Buri Bop. The yellowtail was so buttery and the rice had the right amount of give. My partner had the shrimp pad thai which I thought was just ordinary. The ribs were wonderful but the tuna pizza was just ok. But, I've been eating a lot of ahi lately so admittedly my tongue is bored with it. Overall great experience. Enjoyed the sunset over dinner.

Our server was Mikey, and much like most restaurants we've been to since we arrived, the staff was great - particularly the waiters. We had a busy 16 month old with us and he was her favorite. It wasn't busy when we went (a little early in the evening), so he would stop by our table periodically to chit chat and keep her happy. Very fast getting everything we ordered to the table. Food was good - an elevated version of most Chinese dishes we've had where we are from. The chocolate sphere for dessert was fun and delicious!! Would totally go again!
Service was amazing .mikey made our experience even more special

INCONSISTANT - Iron chefs should know you’re only as good as your last meal.  In this case this is true. Had a fabulous meal on our first visit. Food was great and so was the service and this was reflected in our gratuity.  On our second visit we were very disappointed. The food may have been cooked well but if your table is bombarded with it and you can’t enjoy every dish to the fullest, just means you’re really eating 50% of the meal, and paying for 100% of it.  At $200+ excluding wine for three it’s expensive. Maybe Mr. Morimoto should look at spending some time in his establishments to ensure customer satisfaction instead of leaving it in the hands of those who aren’t capable of fulfilling that promise.  Standards in both service and execution need to be upheld. This is a long standing Japanese tradition, a tradition that ensures perfection on delivery.  Michelin star deserving no. Expensive yes. It’s a gamble at best, and as usual the odds are in the favor of the house.  Looks like Rusty should be a more accurate moniker than Iron in this case and at this rate “seppuku” is appropriate.
Amazing food, amazing service! A must when in Waikiki!! Thanks to Chase & Tommy for providing us with a night to remember!! Highly highly recommend! ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
Excellent Experience. Great Service. Nice Atmosphere. Fantastic Food & Drink!

From beginning to the end of my dining experience the staff was attentive and helpful. I appreciated the staffs recommendations on the food. The desserts here are also a must try. If you want a show, get the Chocolate Sphere!

Ramen was too cold, shrimp fried rice was not fully cooked. Looks nice atmosphere but my daughter got food poisoning after dinner there and went to ER.

Fancy Asian food. It was definitely an experience to eat at Morimoto asian. Their most signature dishes have a process to serving and eating, which was fun and added to the element of your meal. The food was okay, nothing over the top and not worth the price tag. The wait was long, even though i reserved my seats and called ahead of time. We had to wait 30 mins for our seats and about an hour for our food to arrive.  I had the Tonkotsu which was underwhelming. My friend had the Garlic Shrimp which was not fresh, it tasted like frozen shrimp and the shell was very flaky and didn't come apart in one piece. The drinks served there was more ice than drink.  The table service was pretty bad, it seemed under staffed and servers running around like chickens. They were nice and polite but waiting 30 mins+ for our drinks and appetizers was a bit much. The also had table side cooking which filled the whole room with smoke which made dining unpleasant.  I had high hopes for this place because of the name and the location of this place but was let down.  The only saving grace this place has was the melted chocolate dessert, which seems like the only reason people come here for.  Cool experience, but not worth the wait for the food. You will be waiting for a while....
Great Food and Service

My husband and I went for dinner to celebrate our anniversary. When we arrived the hostess told us happy anniversary which was nice. We were seated and the waitress recited a whole paragraph about how they would serve the food one by one and there would be a presentation for each dish. The manager took our food order which seemed as though he did because we were sitting there with our menus closed for a few minutes. Then the waitress came and asked if the manager took our order.  We had to wait for our drinks a little longer than expected and the refills were also very slow and we sat there waiting for our drinks before we could continue eating. There was no special presentation for our food as the waitress presented at the beginning. Our food was just placed down and the table and the server walked away. Hmm what was all that about at the beginning then?  As far as the taste of the food, the fried rice was good and didn't seem like as big of a portion as expensive expected.  Our waitress did nothing for our anniversary as we have seen other reviewers get a complimentary dessert for their anniversary...disappointing when there is nothing to acknowledge a special occasion, especially from a high end restaurant. We didn't even receive an acknowledgement from our waitress.  Not worth the money spent. Lack of communication between staff.
Wonderful staff.  Good customer service and delicious food.

Fantastic experience! My wife and I came here for our 10th anniversary and we loved our time. Kaylee was our server and gave us a ton of information on all the dishes we had questions about. She was cheerful and always prompt in checking in on us and making sure we had everything we needed. Our food was exceptional, especially the ribeye which was cooked perfectly. We will definitely be back on our next trip to Wakiki!

If you search for good food, don’t go there. The orange chicken is already not good and the portion is so small even if they said <<to share>>. In addition, the sorbet was really not good. Above all, kind of expensive for nothing.

Looking for great food and a place for that special occasion? This is worth the splurge (and actually not a splurge for the experience you get and what you pay compared to other restaurants.  Must Try/Known For: Roasted Duck Caesar Salad Eel and Avocado Roll Sticky Ribs Smoked Old Fashion  Why I love it: THE FOOD! You just can’t go wrong with Morimoto. I’ve been to his restaurant in Vegas and it’s just as good. Always consistent. The TABLE SIDE service always adds to the experience (they do it for quite a few of their menu items. Fun and high end vibe. And you can buy a signed copy of his cookbook here!  Price Range ($-$$$$): $$$

Overpriced n I've had way better Chinese food at home/mainland. Even though it's a Japanese billed restaurant/had Thai n Chinese, humn. Small portions also. Hostess stuck up granted she's beautiful, but really? Location was only thing great!

One of my favorite Waikiki eating spots. This is the most polished international level restaurant we found. Amazing menu featuring s range of flavors from across Asia. Every dish was brilliant. Service was the best we’ve come across here. Ambiance was great - we got a table on the balcony which might have been the best spot in the house. Life’s too short to not book a table here.
Breakfast  was delicious pouch eggs on white bread the drink was pine apple juice

If you like good food don't eat here. I give them two stars instead of one because the service was half decent (they accommodated my infant). However, this tastes much like PF Chang's at twice the price. Good food should be challenging to replicate. I could easily cook everything they served us with a recipe. Sad that Chef Morimoto has licensed his brand like this. If you want a real Morimoto experience, go to his restaurant in NYC.

Good food and unique menu but brought down by slow, inconsistent service.  There's no excuse for a 3+ hour dinner, especially 15 minutes for drinks and 30 minutes for dessert.  Also it's an indoor/outdoor seating, but they keep all the doors open so the indoor seats are still uncomfortable and warm.  The food is tasty, if a bit salty, and there's a very wide range in the menu choices.  Portions are small though for the $, so the value could be a little better.

This is a place you must go.  Drinks are wonderful. I recommend the sticky ribs as an appetizer.  So yummy and the meat just falls off the bone. The fried rice with egg is phenomenal.  For dessert, you must have the chocolate sphere. Not only is the dessert delicious, but the presentation should not be missed. They light it on fire and the sphere melts to reveal even more yummy goodness inside.

A hidden treasure! Be sure to go to the 1st floor or you’ll miss this wonderful restaurant. We had a late dinner enjoying the beef carpaccio, yumo! the shrimp har-go then the whole roast duck. Wow what a fabulous night of great food, lovely wine & excellent service from CariAnn. A defiant dining experience when staying in Waikiki Vicki Woods June 2018
Great food, nice atmosphere, friendly service. Good price and portions! Clean and a great view from balcony!

Unfortunately I am upset with the service and management of this restaurant.  My wife and I are staying at this resort on our honeymoon and wanted a nice night out at this new restaurant.  Everything was going great at first, however, a couple was seated next to us and JUST ordered and received their meal before us (we were already seated for 30 minutes and waiting for our main course). We looked over and realized they were served our food. They were already halfway through eating. Only when told, the servers realized their BIG mistake.  Instead of providing immediate service for THEIR mistake, they asked us if we still wanted our food and informed us that it will still be "a while longer". We even heard them joke with the couple next to us if they enjoyed their "extra food".  We received our order another 30 minutes later.  We asked to speak to the manager.. and explained the situation and how it was handled. He offered us free dessert. We refused. He did not charge us for our main meal but only the appetizers and said if we come back we will be "taken care of".  We should have left without paying for anything, but we have more class than that. We paid for our appetizers and even left a tip. We work in the food industry back home and understand the importance of customer service.  We will not be back nor recommend this restaurant. We feel our situation could have been handled with more professionalism.

The restaurant was nice, the presentation of food was very detailed. My wife had the Sashimi salad and it was really tasteless very disappointed. I ordered the Buri bop it is seared tableside. They put a lot of emphasis on this meal as apparently it is the one that the chef won on the iron chef competition show. Overall it's good, would recommend others to try it.
After falling in love with Morimoto Napa, we had to try Morimoto Asia. Amazing food and awesome service. Highly recommend  the Hainanese Chicken Rice.

Awesome all around from bar to table. Great service hostesses to the servers. The killer unexpected ribeye, WOW!

Best black cod on the planet! The service was spot on and every bite I put in my mouth was amazing. We sat outside on the terrace overlooking the ocean. I highly recommend it!
Amazing environment and food!!! Best sushi in long time. Excellent service!!!

Very friendly, professional staff. Nice atmosphere. Good selection of food. My husband tried jellyfish for the first time. It was awesome. Beautiful hotel and restaurant.
Absolutely stunning! Location, food, ambience, service - everything is perfect!

Good food. Little surprised that the menu takes on a Chinese cuisine. Delicious and well priced.

Am unbelievable experience, the food is unique and delightful. Highly recommend the banana pudding for desert so make sure you leave room. The staff are also fantastic and the restraunt has great a layout, a must when visiting Waikiki
We were there on their 2nd day opened.  Food and drinks were great and the staff excelled! The Iron Chef himself was gracious enough for pictures and signed our menus!
Nice place
Overall a great experience. Each plate is beautifully presented and the staff are very friendly and knowledgeable. Would definitely return and try more of the drinks!
Simply amazing! Best meal of my life. The drinks were amazing as well!
Absolutely amazing food! Service was great and all the staff were lovely.
Really enjoyed the food and atmosphere I didn't know that the sun set everyday at 6:41 but the manager did

So we were staying at the Alohilani hotel and that restaurant is located in it. The view from the outdoor tables is just beautiful!! The food wasn't expensive at all and I thought such a great place would be more pricey. We have ordered the Cobia fish carpaccio for an appetizer, two rolls of sushi and a whole fish for two people, and it was a perfect amount. Loved all the dishes that we got like it was made for our taste. Our server was that little asian looking girl with a little dark skin and she was really sweet I forgot her name but if you see her tip her well! Didn't have enough room for desert this time but I've seen some of the deserts other people ordered and they looked awesome.
Sticky ribs were incredible! Tuna pizza good. Wine ok Ambient ok I liked it, but i was not thrilled to be honest.
Our favourite restaurant in Waikiki, stunning to watch the sun go down. Amazing food and service, and a wonderful place to be proposed to 😍💍
Amazing service and food was absolutely perfection
Great atmosphere, delicious tonkatsu ramen.  Good menu selection and very attentive staff.
Was denied a table that no one was sitting at. But hey the waiters and waitresses needed a place to watch the parade. Horrible service. Maybe Hy's Steak house will appreciate me more.

Delicious. Tried the edamame which was basic but loved trying the jelly Fish. Dinner and appetizer were excellent. Idk what I got for dinner but it was with vegetables. Server was good and friendly but once it got busy we barely saw him. The guys filling up the water were so friendly and more helpful than the server at times.
Great service, good prices, excellent food.

I used to live in Hawaii a few years ago and have come back just about every year. This restaurant is by far the best restaurant (in terms of quality and night atmosphere) I’ve ever been to on Oahu.  My husband and I came out to enjoy the casual and low key lifestyle of Hawaii but after a week, missed something a little nicer and wanted to try this place out.  We’re very accustomed to the city life of Denver and it’s upscale restaurants... I would say that the food, presentation, and service here blows all of those overly priced, fancy steakhouses out of the water!  We had the orange chicken and kalbi. Both were cooked PERFECTLY. The Kalbi METLED in my my mouth (very uncommon, couldn’t believe it) and the breading on the orange chicken had an amazing after taste (didn’t even know that was possible).  The plain white rice was even soft!!! I’m Asian American, I thought rice was basically cooked and tasted the exact same way haha  Our server CariAnn and everyone helping her were remarkable. They were very attentive and always smiling.  We will definitely be back when we’re on Oahu.
Sticky ribs and buri bop were incredible! Great service, clean & chic decor. Got busy, rsvp recommended!
Had a wonderful evening here. The food was to die for. The carpaccio melted in my mouth, and Morimoto's famous orange chicken is worth the drive. Prices were very reasonable!

I was excited to get a reservation for this newly opened restaurant in time for my 5 year wedding anniversary (and babymoon) on our Hawaii trip! We were seated on the balcony next to some obvious VIPs as they arrived after us to complimentary glasses of rose on their table while we waited and waited only to have my pregnant wife's virgin cocktail arrive with alcohol. By the time the correct drink had arrived, our VIP neighbours had already been visited by the manager and received their appetisers. The head chef had come out and cooked the VIP's table side dish himself before our appetisers finally arrived a full hour after we had been seated.... except they were stone cold dim sum. Despite the manager offering his business card so we could email him if we wanted them to make up for the experience, we left and headed to the Cheesecake factory for a delicious, well priced meal with honest, good service. I'm aware the restaurant had only been open for a few days but I expected more from an establishment with the Morimoto name.
It is really nice. My dad works there. My favorite is the orange chicken.👌follow me on instagram at (Hawaiian.b) look for the cat 👌 I need more followers thank you🤗
